About three things I was absolutely positive:
First, Edward was a vampire.
Second, there was a part of him--and I didnÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢t know how dominant that part might be--that thirsted for my blood.
And third, I was unconditionally and irrevocably in love with him.


This series gets too much hate.  Yes, the characters are overblown and the story is convoluted.  Yes, Bella doesn't act like a normal teenager, but point out a 'normal teenager' for me and I'll drop this argument right now.  But despite all the flaws, this is still a great novel series and the films are FUN.  The first film is no where near as good as the second, and the third coming out soon to theaters actually has the most potential for being really good.  But overall, the films are still great entertainment when compared to the Reality TV that's being pumped at us nonstop ...

Now, I used the EXACT same Twilight.mp4 file as I previously uploaded and even let the original torrent do a hash-check.  In fact, I'm actually uploading to BOTH torrent files simultaneously.  If you HAVE the first torrent, I ask that you help out by uploading the first film while downloading the second.  It will make the torrent move that much quicker.  I've even put the New Moon.mp4 into the same folder, which will make things that much easier.

Basically, this is just an updated torrent with the second film added.  If all goes well and this torrent stays seeded, then next year I'll probably end up updating it again for Eclipse.  I also decided NOT to post any trivia up for these films, mostly because fans of the series know most of the trivia anyway.  And yes ... that last screen shot is from the very, very end when Bella is finally speechless.  


